      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <p><pb n="1v"/><!-- 
This is not explicitly stated anywhere I've read, but I assume that these double plates, each inscribed on one face only, use 1verso and 2 recto, with the blank side of each plate facing outward. 
--><lb n="1"/><g type="mangala"/>svasty<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> uccakalp<unclear>ā</unclear>n mahārājaughadeva<space type="binding-hole"/>s tasya puttras tat-pādānudhyāto mahādevyā<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied><!-- 
The maṅgala symbol seems to be a short horizontal dash at the height of the upper baseline. It is at the margin. 
--><lb n="2"/>kumāradevyām utpanno mahārāja-kumāradevas tasya putt<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied>as tat-pādānudhyāto
<lb n="3"/>mahādevyā<unclear>ṁ</unclear> jayasvāminyām utpanno mahārāja-jayasvāmī tasya puttras tat-pādā<lb break="no" n="4"/>nudhyāto mahādevyāṁ rāmadevyām utpanno mahārāja-vyāghras tasya puttras tat-pādānudhyā<lb break="no" n="5"/>to mahādevyām ajjhitadevyām utpan<supplied reason="omitted">n</supplied>o mahārāja-jayanāthas tasya puttras tat-pādānu<lb break="no" n="6"/>dhyāto mahādevyā<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> muruṇḍasvāminyām utpanno mahārāja-śarvvanāthaḥ kuśalī maṇi<lb break="no" n="7"/>nāga-peṭhe vyāghrapallika-kācarapallika-grāmayo<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied> brāhmaṇādīn prativāsinaḥ
<lb n="8"/>samājñāpayati</p>
        <p>vidita<unclear>ṁ</unclear> vo stu <choice>
            <sic>yathaiṣa</sic>
            <corr>yathaitau</corr>
          </choice> grāmau mayā sodraṅgau soparikarau <lb n="9"/>A-cāṭa-bhaṭa-<choice>
            <sic>prāveśyo</sic>
            <corr>prāveśyau</corr>
          </choice> rājābhāvya-sarva-kara-pratyāy<choice>
            <sic>e</sic>
            <corr>o</corr>
          </choice>tpannakotpadyamānaka-sam<choice>
            <sic>o</sic>
            <corr>e</corr>
          </choice><!-- 
I accept Fleet's authority that samo was really engraved; to me the additional mātrā looks like just a scratch at the edge of the plate. 
--><lb break="no" n="10"/>tau Ācandrārkka-samakālikau cora-<choice>
            <sic>t</sic>
            <corr>d</corr>
          </choice>aṇḍa-varjjitau pulindabhaṭasya pras<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>dīkr̥tau<lb n="11"/>tenāpi mānapure kāritaka-deva-kul<unclear>e</unclear> bhagavatyāḥ <choice>
            <sic>paṣṭhapurikā</sic>
            <corr>piṣṭapurikā</corr>
          </choice>-devyāḥ pūjā-ni<lb break="no" n="12"/>mittaṁ khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-pratisaṁskaraṇāya ca kumārasvāmine putra-pautrānvayopa<lb break="no" n="13"/>bhojy<choice>
            <sic>o</sic>
            <corr>au</corr>
          </choice> pratipāditau<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> mayāpi bhūmi-cchidr<choice>
            <sic>ā</sic>
            <corr>a</corr>
          </choice>-nyāyena tāmra-śāsan<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>e</corr>
          </choice>nānumoditau</p>
        <p><lb n="14"/>te yūyam evopalabhyājñā-śravaṇa-vidheyā bhūtvā samucita-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇyā<lb break="no" n="15"/>vātāy<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>di-pratyāyān upaneṣyatha<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><!-- 
Line 15 is about half the length of the earlier lines. The text slants downward, so the remaining space in l15 is vertically challenged. 
--><pb n="2r"/><lb n="16"/>y<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>e</corr>
          </choice> cāsmad-va<sic>n</sic>śotpadyamānaka-rājānas tair i<space type="binding-hole"/>yaṁ datti<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied> nna vilopyā yathā-kāla<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> sa<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied>varddha<lb break="no" n="17"/>nīyānumodanīyā pratipālanīyā ca<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> <space type="binding-hole"/>rājābhāvya-kara-pratyāyā<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> sarvve na grāhyā<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><!-- 
Fleet understands rāja-a-bhāvya, "taxes which by custom should not belong to the king". I'm not sure about this but haven't checked. If we take rājā as standing for rāja, then there should be a hyphen at the end of the line. 
--><lb n="18"/>yaś caitāṁ dattiṁ lopayet saḫ pañcabhir mahā-pātakair upapātakaiś ca saṁyukto bhūyā<lb break="no" n="19"/>d<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> uktañ ca mahābhārate śatasāhasry<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>ṁ saṁhitāyāṁ paramarṣiṇā parāśara-sutena<lb break="no" n="20"/>veda-vyāsena vyāsena</p>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="1">
          <l n="a">pūrvva-dattām dvijātibhyo</l>
          <l n="b">yatnād rakṣa yudhiṣṭhira</l>
          <l n="c">mahī<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> <sic>mahi</sic><lb break="no" n="21"/><sic>vatā</sic> śreṣṭha</l>
          <l n="d">dānāc chreyo nupālanaM<!-- 
The halanta m is very unclear in the facsimile, but seems to be a small subscript form without a line above. 
--></l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="2">
          <l n="a">prāyeṇa hi narendrāṇāṁ</l>
          <l n="b">vidyate n<choice>
              <sic>a</sic>
              <corr>ā</corr>
            </choice>śubhā <lb n="22"/>gatiḥ</l>
          <l n="c">pūya<choice>
              <sic>t</sic>
              <corr>n</corr>
            </choice>te te <choice>
              <sic>tta</sic>
              <corr>tu</corr>
            </choice> satataṁ</l>
          <l n="d">prayacchanto vasu<supplied reason="omitted">ndharāM</supplied></l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="3">
          <l n="a"><supplied reason="omitted">bahubhir vasu</supplied>dhā bhuktā</l>
          <l n="b">rājabhis sagarādibhi<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied><!-- 
Grand eyeskip in l22. 
--></l>
          <l n="c"><lb n="23"/>yasya yasya yadā bhūmis</l>
          <l n="d">tasya tasya tadā phalaM<!-- 
The halanta m is very unclear in the facsimile, but seems to be a small subscript form without a line above. 
--></l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="4">
          <l n="a">ṣaṣṭi-varṣa-sahasrāṇi</l>
          <l n="b"><lb n="24"/>svargge modati bhūmidaḥ</l>
          <l n="c">Ākṣeptā cānumantā ca</l>
          <l n="d">tāny eva narake vaseT<!-- 
The halanta t is very unclear in the facsimile, but seems to be a small non-subscript form. 
--></l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="5">
          <l n="a">sva-da<lb n="25"/>ttāṁ para-dattāṁ vā</l>
          <l n="b">yo hareta vasundharā<unclear>M</unclear></l>
          <!-- 
Fleet supplies an anusvāra at the end. In the facsimile I see some space after rā, with a couple of specks in it. Given that the plates have been using halanta consonants at the ends of verses (though not at half-verses so far), I think the space and specks are the remnants of a halanta M. 
-->
          <l n="c">śva-viṣṭhāyāṁ kr̥mir bhūtvā</l>
          <l n="d">pitr̥bhis saha <lb n="26"/>majjati</l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="5">
          <l n="a">apānīyeṣv araṇyeṣu</l>
          <l n="b">śuṣka-koṭara-vāsinaḥ</l>
          <l n="c">kr̥ṣṇāhayo hi jā<lb n="27"/>yaṁte</l>
          <l n="d">pūrvva-dāyaṁ haranti ye</l>
        </lg>
        <p>likhitaṁ sa<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied>vatsara-śata-dvaye caturddaśottare <lb n="28"/>pauṣa-māsa-divase ṣa<choice>
            <sic>p</sic>
            <corr>ṣ</corr>
          </choice>ṭhe ph<sic>a</sic>lgudattāmātya-pranapt<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied>ā varāhadin<supplied reason="omitted">n</supplied>a-napt<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied>ā<!-- 
See comment on IN00084/21 about the name ph(a/ā)lgudatta. 
--><lb n="29"/>manoratha-sutena sāndhiviggrahika-nāthena<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> dūtako dhr̥tisvāmikaḥ</p>
